    "causal_summary": "Two mature open-source memory engines are vendored under `external/` — galadriel (Python memory-palace) and aionforge-memory (Rust retrieval substrate). They encode retrieval, consolidation, and currentness techniques that the project's own four retrieval subsystems do not yet use. Without a structured mining effort, that prior art stays unread and the internal systems keep their known gaps (no query-class routing, flag-based currentness, write-blocking consolidation, non-deterministic fusion).",
